commitResults.messageBody:
TommyTalks does not save tasks, causing users to restart their lists of
tasks every session.

Adding a storage class to keep track of tasks improves user-experience
since it makes the app more practical.

Changes have been made in branch-Level-7 regarding data storage.

To update master branch, we will do a merge commit with branch-Level-7.

commitResults.messageBody:
Find feature has been added in branch-Level-9.

To update master branch, we will do a merge commit with branch-Level-9.

There are no assertions in the source code.

Adding insertions can help to reduce bugs by ensuring assumptions made
by programmer is held throughout the execution of the program.

Let's add some assertions at key points throughout the code to document
these assumptions.

Using assertions is easy to integrate into our code to ensure our
assumptions hold true.

Assertions have been added in Storage and TaskCommand class.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code to fit Code Quality standards
commitResults.messageBody:
Code does not follow Code Quality standards closely.

Code that is written to different standards can make it harder to read
and follow along when being reviewed by peers, hence we should aim to
improve the readability of the code and follow an agreed-upon coding
standard.

Let's refactor the code to follow the SE-EDU Java coding standard.

The SE-EDU Java coding standard is the agreed standard to follow by the
course, so we should follow this instead of relying on our intuition.

Refer to the SE-EDU Java coding standards at
https://se-education.org/guides/conventions/java/intermediate.html
Refactor code to fit Code Quality standards

commitResults.messageBody:
Branch-A-Assertions is out of date with master branch after master
merged with branch-A-CodeQuality.

To continue working on branch-A-Assertion, we should update
branch-A-Assertions to reduce conflicts.

Let's merge master to branch-A-Assertion.

This is to update branch-A-Assertion in the cleanest way possible.

There are not much assertions present.

We may not be addressing the implicit assumptions enough, so we should
include more checks throughout the code.

Let's add some more assertions throughout the code.

Assertions provide a better way to check for underlying conditions
compared to if else statements.

Tasks were ordered based on order of insertion, and could not be edited
further.

User may have preferences on the ordering of the tasks, thus they may
want to be able to order the tasks according to their preferences.

Let's add a priority attribute to Task objects, and allow for users to
be able to sort the current task list based on this attribute.

Using the comparator interface allows for tasks objects to have a
natural ordering, allowing for easier sorting.

On top of adding sort and priority feature, also modified .gitignore to
stop tracking test txt files.
